HEADWORD: Lachrymals
<hw>Lach"ry*mals</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[<er>See
Lachrymal</er>.]</ety> <def>Tears; also, lachrymal feelings or
organs.</def> <mark>[Colloq.]</mark></p>

<p><q>People go to the theaters to have . . . their risibles and
<qex>lachrymals</qex> set agoing.</q> <rj><qau>The
Lutheran.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lachrymary</ent>⟦br⟧
